<!-- Concorde autopilot :

     - Speed with pitch and Mach with pitch are considered autopilot modes (datum).
     - Speed with throttle limited to 0.980 (climb rating).
     - Mach with throttle limited to 0.967 (cruise rating).
     - restoring to /vertical/vertical-speed-fps (see Concorde-init-instrumentation.xml) 
     doesn't require a new tuning of autopilot.


     TO DO :
     =====
     - u_max cannot be controlled by engine rating.
     - 1 PID per throttle with autoland (glide slope and vertical speed with throttle).


     Known problems :
     ==============
     - nav hold doesn't use /autopilot/internal/nav1-track-error-deg, because approach has
     a discrepancy with /instrumentation/nav/heading-needle-deflection, only solved in
     the last 700 ft (GPS computes /instrumentation/gps/indicated-track-true-deg with
     an offset, 0.3 degrees a KSFO), causing a roll at 500 ft AGL during autoland. 
     - roll on heading hold above Mach 1.0 (first PID only) : might be the FDM (?).
     Solved by a rudder trim, which unlocks the roll at Mach speeds.
     - increasing sensitivity reduces waddling at Mach 2 : 1 subsonic PID and
     1 supersonic PID.
     - a lookahead 8 s could accelerate the convergence of heading hold.
     But that creates roll oscillations, around 800 ft AGL during autoland (nav1),
     with turbulence (ins), and during the transition to magnetic heading hold (vor and ins).  
-->

<!-- Each component is evaluated in the order specified.  You can make up -->
<!-- property names to pass the result of one component on to a subsequent -->
<!-- component. -->


